comment: Reed (MIA) beats Lopez (BKN) to the spot and obtains a legal guarding position.
White (MIA) sets a screen while out of bounds.
Reed (MIA) and Lopez (BKN) briefly engage and separate during rebounding.
Reed (MIA) does not maintain a legal vertical position and turns sideways, making contact with LeVert's (BKN) body that affects his driving shot attempt.
Lopez (BKN) sets the screen on Dragic (MIA) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
[Detectable with stop watch] Booker (BKN) is in the paint for longer than three seconds.
Booker (BKN) dislodges White (MIA), affecting his ability to retrieve the rebound.
Waiters (MIA) makes incidental contact with Foye (BKN) that does not affect his SQBR.
Booker (BKN) sets the screen on Waiters (MIA) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Dragic (MIA) makes marginal contact with Booker (BKN) on the driving shot attempt.
Reed (MIA) sets the screen on Foye (BKN) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Foye (BKN) legally contests Waiters' (MIA) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Lopez (BKN) sets the screen on Waiters (MIA) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Waiters (MIA) legally contests Foye's (BKN) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Dinwiddie (BKN) commits a take foul on Ellington (MIA).
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the floor that Dinwiddie (BKN) released the field goal attempt prior to the game clock expiring is confirmed.
